aVPolice are investigating a death after they found a 70-year-old woman dead inside a church fellowship hall.\u000a\u000aPolice say they found Ruthie Carolyn New, 70, in the fellowship hall at Denham Street Baptist Church in Somerset.\u000a\u000aThe pastor of the church found her body around 3:40 p.m. Relatives filed a missing person report 30 minutes earlier.\u000a\u000aFamily members say New was the widow of the former pastor at this church and a charter member.\u000a\u000aWe are told she also cleaned the church on Thursdays, and that's what they believe she was doing at the church before her death.\u000a\u000a"It's a tightly knit church, tightly knit community. You just want to pray for them pray for the family and pray for this entire community that's been affected by this. It's a sad situation," said Somerset Police Department PIO, Mike Correll.\u000a\u000aPolice say they are investigating New's death as a homicide. Investigators are not releasing the cause or manner of death because they say that information is crucial to their case.\u000a\u000aAn autopsy is scheduled for Friday in Frankfort.
