aVCNN Beats MSNBC in Total Day and Prime Time Demos for 26th Straight Month\u000a\u000aNetwork Grows More than +50% Compared to Last Year\u000a\u000aPrime Time Programming Grew Up to 83%\u000a\u000aNew Day is Up 64%\u000a\u000aCNN Ranks #1 at 4am, 5am, 2pm, 3pm, 4pm\u000a\u000aCNN ranked #2 in cable news in August, topping MSNBC in both total day and prime time demos (adults 25-54) for the 26th straight month. This represents the longest winning streak over MSNBC in six years in total day and eight years in prime time.\u000a\u000aCNN also beat MSNBC in total viewers for the month in total day and was the ninth most-watched network in all of cable for the month.\u000a\u000aCNN\u2019s viewership grew double digits this month, increasing more than 50 percent in total day and more than 40 percent in prime time compared to last August. FULL POST
