aVCNN International today announced that Dubai-based global developer Emaar Properties is to sponsor \u2018One Square Meter\u2019, a new weekly segment within CNN\u2019s nightly \u2018Global Exchange\u2019 show exploring the ever-changing landscape of real estate in emerging markets.\u000a\u000aThe sponsorship will position Emaar in front of CNN\u2019s upscale online and television audience across Europe, Middle East, Africa; Asia; South Asia and Latin America.\u000a\u000aThe campaign package includes: sponsorship of editorial series \u201cOne Square Meter\u201d via billboard, and corporate commercials around the series; sponsorship of editorial vignettes based on the series with \u2018in association\u2019 opening and closing billboards; sponsored TV promos; co-branded banners, and a dedicated microsite www.cnn.com/onesquaremeter, with digital banner execution across all sites including CNN Arabic and CNN International.\u000a\u000aKaterina Tornari, Account Director EMEA, CNN International said: \u201cWe\u2019re delighted that Emaar has chosen to broaden its connection with CNN International\u2019s audience through this cross-platform campaign. The sponsorship is a fresh dimension to previous advertising they have done with CNN and gives them the opportunity to put their brand messaging in front of the key business decision maker audience we can guarantee to deliver.\u201d\u000a\u000aAhmad Al Matrooshi, Managing Director, Emaar Properties, said: \u201cThe pioneer of integrated master-planned communities in Dubai, Emaar has a strong portfolio of projects in several key emerging markets in the Middle East and North Africa region and the Indian Subcontinent. Our developments focus on energising local economies through a focus not just on property but also by building robust hospitality and mall assets. \u2018One Square Meter\u2019 on CNN International\u2019s \u2018Global Exchange\u2019 highlights the impact of the real estate sector on emerging markets, and through our support, we are focused on further strengthening our brand equity across a wide international audience.\u201d\u000a\u000aAbout \u2018One Square Meter\u2019\u000a\u000a\u2018One Square Meter\u2019 will explore leading architectural designs, city plans and demand for property internationally to help inform viewers and potential investors in international markets.\u000a\u000a\u2018One Square Meter\u2019 airs as a segment every Tuesday within \u2018Global Exchange\u2019, CNN International\u2019s prime time business show which airs Sunday to Thursday at 1600 GMT / 2000 UAE.\u000a\u000awww.cnn.com/onesquaremeter\u000a\u000aFor further information, please contact:\u000a\u000aZeina Jamra\u000a\u000aCNN International\u000a\u000a+971 4 4467714\u000a\u000aZeina.jamra@turner.com\u000a\u000aAbout CNN in the Middle East\u000a\u000aCNN is the leading international news brand in the Middle East (EMS Middle East June 2012). Its regional operations include the CNN Abu Dhabi bureau which opened in November 2009 and the CNNArabic.com website which launched in January 2002. Its programming remit from the region includes the feature shows \u2018Inside the Middle East\u2019 and \u2018CNN Marketplace Middle East\u2019 and the nightly \u2018Global Exchange\u2019 programme. CNN\u2019s regional bureaux include Abu Dhabi, Beirut, Cairo, Istanbul and Jerusalem.\u000a\u000aAbout CNN International\u000a\u000aCNN\u2019s portfolio of news and information services is available in five different languages across all major TV, internet and mobile platforms reaching more than 375 million households around the globe. CNN International, awarded \u201cNews Channel of the Year\u201d by the Royal Television Society in March 2013, is the number one international TV news channel according to all major media surveys across Europe, the Middle East and Africa, the Asia Pacific region and Latin America. The CNN digital network is consistently one of the top news and current affairs destination on the web. CNN has